Plotting Conditional Summaries

Notes:

pf.fc_by_age_gender <- 
  subset(pf,!is.na(gender)) %>%
    group_by(age,gender) %>%
    summarise (mean_friend_count = mean(friend_count),
               median_friend_count = median(friend_count),
               n = n()
    )
                  

ggplot(data = pf.fc_by_age_gender, aes(x = age, y = median_friend_count, group = gender, 
                                       colour = gender)) +
              geom_line(size = 1)+
              xlab("Age")+
              ylab ("Median Friend Count")+
              ggtitle("Age vs Median Friend Count")+
              theme(legend.position="bottom")

Reshaping Data

Notes:

#install.packages('reshape2')

suppressMessages(library(reshape2))

#dcast is used because we want to cast it as a dataframe

pf.fc_by_age_gender.wide <- dcast(pf.fc_by_age_gender,
                                  age ~ gender,
                                  value.var = "median_friend_count")

# The linetype parameter can take the values 0-6:
# 0 = blank, 1 = solid, 2 = dashed
# 3 = dotted, 4 = dotdash, 5 = longdash
# 6 = twodash

mygraph <- ggplot(data = pf.fc_by_age_gender.wide, aes(x = age, y = female/male))+
  geom_line(color = "dark blue", size = 1)+
  geom_hline(yintercept = 1 , linetype = 2 , size = 0.5)

mygraph

Third Quantitative Variable

Notes:

pf$year_joined = floor(2014 - pf$tenure/365) 

summary(pf$year_joined)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max.    NA's 
##    2005    2012    2012    2012    2013    2014       2
#?cut

pf$year_joined.bucket <- cut(pf$year_joined,c(2004, 2009, 2011, 2012, 2014))

Bias-Variance Tradeoff Revisited

Notes:

ggplot(aes(x = tenure, y = friendships_initiated / tenure),
       data = subset(pf, tenure >= 1)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = year_joined.bucket),
            stat = 'summary',
            fun.y = mean)

ggplot(aes(x = 7 * round(tenure / 7), y = friendships_initiated / tenure),
       data = subset(pf, tenure > 0)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = year_joined.bucket),
            stat = "summary",
            fun.y = mean)

ggplot(aes(x = 30 * round(tenure / 30), y = friendships_initiated / tenure),
       data = subset(pf, tenure > 0)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = year_joined.bucket),
            stat = "summary",
            fun.y = mean)

ggplot(aes(x = 90 * round(tenure / 90), y = friendships_initiated / tenure),
       data = subset(pf, tenure > 0)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = year_joined.bucket),
            stat = "summary",
            fun.y = mean)

ggplot(aes(x = tenure, y = friendships_initiated / tenure),
       data = subset(pf, tenure >= 1)) +
  geom_smooth(aes(color = year_joined.bucket))
## geom_smooth: method="auto" and size of largest group is >=1000, so using gam with formula: y ~ s(x, bs = "cs"). Use 'method = x' to change the smoothing method.

#?transform

yo$all.purchases <- yo$strawberry + yo$blueberry + yo$pina.colada + yo$plain + yo$mixed.berry

ggplot(data = yo, aes(x = all.purchases)) + geom_histogram(binwidth = 1)

  geom_line()+
  facet_wrap( ~id)

Heat Maps

Notes:

nci <- read.table("nci.tsv")
colnames(nci) <- c(1:64)
nci.long.samp <- melt(as.matrix(nci[1:200,]))
names(nci.long.samp) <- c("gene", "case", "value")
head(nci.long.samp)
##   gene case  value
## 1    1    1  0.300
## 2    2    1  1.180
## 3    3    1  0.550
## 4    4    1  1.140
## 5    5    1 -0.265
## 6    6    1 -0.070
ggplot(aes(y = gene, x = case, fill = value),
  data = nci.long.samp) +
  geom_tile() +
  scale_fill_gradientn(colours = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "red"))(100))
